description: This file defines a mock class CloudStoreImplementationMock used for unit testing, which mocks the interfaces related to cloud storage operations such as setting, getting, deleting keys and namespaces, and managing storage limits. It includes mock methods to simulate behavior for testing purposes within the project.

classes.name: CloudStoreImplementationMock
classes.description: Mock class for cloud storage interfaces used for unit testing, supporting multiple inheritance from various store-related interfaces.

methods.name: ~CloudStoreImplementationMock
methods.description: Default destructor for the mock class.

methods.name: Register
methods.description: Mocks the registration of notifications for store events.

methods.name: Unregister
methods.description: Mocks the unregistration of notifications for store events.

methods.name: SetValue
methods.description: Mocks setting a value in the store with namespace and key.

methods.name: GetValue
methods.description: Mocks retrieving a value from the store.

methods.name: DeleteKey
methods.description: Mocks deleting a specific key from the store.

methods.name: Register
methods.description: Mocks the registration for IStore2 notifications.

methods.name: Unregister
methods.description: Mocks the unregistration for IStore2 notifications.

methods.name: SetValue
methods.description: Mocks setting a scoped value in the store with TTL (time-to-live).

methods.name: GetValue
methods.description: Mocks retrieving a scoped value and its TTL.

methods.name: DeleteNamespace
methods.description: Mocks deleting a namespace within a scope.

methods.name: GetKeys
methods.description: Mocks retrieving keys within a scope and namespace.

methods.name: GetNamespaces
methods.description: Mocks retrieving available namespaces within a scope.

methods.name: GetStorageSizes

methods.name: GetNamespaceStorageLimit
methods.description: Mocks retrieving storage limit for a namespace.

methods.name: SetNamespaceStorageLimit
methods.description: Mocks setting storage limit for a namespace.
